text: Valerio Grazini (born 26 September 1992) is an Italian sport shooter. ==Biography== He participated, from 2009 to 2019, at nine editions of the ISSF World Shooting Championships and won six medals at international senior level and five with the team. ==References== ==External links== * Category:Living people Category:1992 births Category:Italian male sport shooters Category:Trap and double trap shooters Category:People from Viterbo Category:Universiade gold medalists for Italy Category:Universiade silver medalists for Italy Category:Universiade medalists in shooting Category:European Games competitors for Italy Category:Shooters at the 2019 European Games Category:European Games medalists in shooting Category:European Games silver medalists for Italy Category:Shooters of Centro Sportivo Carabinieri Category:Medalists at the 2013 Summer Universiade Category:Medalists at the 2015 Summer Universiade
